reviews.text: very impressive botanical gardens. massive variety of plants and trees. probably the nicest place near/in the city to go for a picnic. you can easily spend the whole day here if u want to see everything. there is a nice/busy cafe by the pond and a seed and plant shop where occasionally u can find rare plants and seeds. theres also another shop which sells great local original watercolour paintings of plants and flowers and other nice stuff. 5 stars

Absolutely DO NOT MISS THIS!! FABULOUS trees, birds, 3 must see buildings. A health Garden rose gardens. It smells good and, free!!  We spent 3 hours. Ending with a tour (and nice glass!) Of The Australian Wine Center 👍👍

Beautiful and peaceful garden. The glass house is impressive and the cactus and succulents trail has very nice specimens. Lots of grazed area where you can sit and relax by the ponds. I highly recommend!

We nearly missed the gardens because it is the Botanical Park that is closed for maintenance. Fortunately we talked to a helpful person in the zoo kiosk who advised us to try another entrance. Don't miss the flying foxes in the trees either.The gardens are well laid out with plenty of shade and a few exhibition houses- some modern others art deco design.Very peaceful away from the city and slightly cooler in places.A gem in the city and must see.

An amazing collection of fauna. Some truly impressive plants and all so nicely laid out. Spend an hour or two at least it's well worth it. There are a few canteen /kiosks and the have surprising range of choices. The birds flying amongst the visitors are pretty.

In a city that is devoid of any cultural depth. This is a shining beacon of what the place can achieve... A beautiful building with well thought out exhibition spaces and a nice venue for the day explore all the level! Great work Adelaide arts!!

The best galleries are in the basement of the building at least that is where the temporary shows are. 
The permanent collection is housed on the ground floor. 
The Cafe and restaurant is on the back of the building.
I especially like the galleries collection of contemporary Australian art which they collected lots of starting I'm the late 70's it seems.
Excellent place to drop into.

Always wonderful exhibitions. Ben Quilty one was amazing and I am glad I didn't miss it and that the Art Gallery puts on such a diverse set of works, on top of a lot of their already wonderful pieces. Also... it's free!

One of Australia's best. Loved the gallery installations, the Picasso exhibition and the drawing room behind the exhibition. Amazing and lived the spaces as always!! Well worth a visit. Do not miss if you are in Adelaide. A cultural thumbs up in the whole Australian landscape. Do not dismiss one of Australia's most innovative states. If you don't believe me, take a look at SA history. You will be surprised.

I love this gallery. It has some wonderful art works, carefully and cleverly curated, with regular special exhibitions. For its size, it's outstanding.
It also has a nice cafe/restaurant. Try the Bush bubbles - sparkling wine with pepperberry syrup - it's delicious.

This place surprised us with how good it is. 3 floors and several areas exploring the different connections of people to the sea in SA. Some highlights... A small merchant sailing ship you can actually walk onto/into. Reconstruction of the living/sleeping quarters of migrant ships of the 1800's.
Great place to visit with so much history to be found. I have been here a few times and find something different to amaze me each time. The kids absolutely loved it.

Nicely done museum with great information about the maritime history of South Australia. Lots of physical displays and interactive elements to keep people engaged. Located in a nice old building in the historical precinct of Port Adelaide.

Great place to bring the kids. Lots to do and learn and the school holiday activities they run are lots of fun even for the parents too. The staff are really lovely and the gift shop has lots of great things to buy.
This is an amazing museum. It's bigger than what you think, you could spend hours here looking around. Very cheap entry which gives you discount entry to other museums in the Port.
Different and modern structure. Good variety of plants, but nothing exotic or different. Pretty calm and peaceful inside.

If you are really interested in plants then it's a good place for an afternoon side trip whilst in the botanic gardens but I didn't see many new or unusual plants. The structure is nice and the layout is very easy to get through but I feel like a lot of people would walk through in 5 minutes and be done. Not many orchids for a tropical environment but I suppose the focus is Australian tropical
Great day out...picnic or walking
Tropical paradise with big spiders!
Fabulous resource in the city, a quiet place to reflect

Absolutely worth the trip up there in the hills. Saw a number of wild lives and met my objective of trekking to the conservation park. Great job for keeping this park accessible and still livable for the local wildlife. Will be back if I have the chance.
Picnics here are awesome 10/10 would meme again
Its a very nice place for a quick hike. It has 3 waterfalls. If you are lucky you can see some of the animals while hiking. It can be a gateway from your boredom on a nice bright sunny day

Absolutely worth the trip up there in the hills. Saw a number of wild lives and met my objective of trekking to the conservation park. Great job for keeping this park accessible and still livable for the local wildlife. Will be back if I have the chance.
Great park with stunning canyons. Even saw some kangaroos quite close. (Here comes the obvious...)- Just be aware that the waterfall is very dependent on recent rainfall/amount.

I love this place so much! The waterfall is amazing, and the hikes are so interesting. So much wildlife, makes every second enjoyable. A playground which incorporates nature makes it a perfect picnicking spot!
Incredible quality food that you can't stop eating even when full. I recommend getting a banquet. Favorite place to eat in Adelaide.

Consistently delicious, quick food delivery, and the entire place is run by one chef and one waiter on the floor. Best falafel in adelaide. Best beans and rice in adelaide. Best hummus in adelaide. Best baklava. Best everything! Do yourself a favour and come het and get a bargain banquet for $25 with free BYO!
Delicious food - definitely get the banquet! BYO with no corkage when ordering the banquet if spending $22+ per person. Bring cash - no split bills or card payments.
Banquet was brilliant, with plenty of food. Coffee is Devine also. Laid back attitude isn't to be confused with not caring, this place is awesome. Either drop in and est or pick and take away.
About as unpretentious and down market as you could possibly get, but still has great food giving a really good feed.

Great food and service. Harry and his team make it a truly authentic Indian experience. I requested the chefs recommendation and was not disappointed.  Will be bringing the family back very soon . Thank you
Great food..great services. ..I have been there 4 time and will definitely going again. .
Good service with nice people in the front. Excellent value for money
Tasty indian food with generous portions for a fair price.
tasty fresh indian food that they will make to suit you, you can choose how spicy you wan't it and all the meals are made with care. Great chef and atmosphere, highly recommend.
We love this place. We have eaten here 3 or 4 times and have been impressed every time. The staff are lovely, they never mess up an order and the food is delicious. Would highly recommend.

This place is fantastic!
The Customer service was exquisite.
They pulled the seat out for you, pour your drinks at the table.
They where extremely friendly and helpful.
I can't fault the food, everything we ordered was perfect.
The hot pot was so huge, I couldent finish it but they have takeaway containers.
100% would go there again
My favourite Japanese restaurant in Adelaide. Food and service is impeccable. Very family friendly and cosy atmosphere.
Can't understand why more people don't come here.  Lady running the joint is very entertaining and we've had standard but excellent food every time we've been.
My board had dinner there this week, were a little hesitant about the ambience , but were completely won over by the quality of the food and the service.

My Partner and I go to Kenji Modern Japanese each year for our Anniversary because we love it so much and love to splurge on the menu here.  Their mixed Entrees have always been fantastic, food is always delicious with fresh ingredients.  I definitely recommend the Pork Belly!  

The only thing I'm sad about is that my favourite dessert items are gone from their menu now :(

Exquisitely modern, delicious, calm, and vego/vegan-friendly. My wife (non-vego) and I both love going here: in fact, it's our favourite date-night venue. The zensai entree is a delight. We've never been disappointed by the food or the service.
Such an amazing degustation experience, for the eyes, and the palette. Food to make your taste buds sing.

Another delicious, innovative, and hospitable night last night. Across 3 courses for two people (one vegan), delight for both eye and palate. And some enticing dishes passing by for next time! Ethereal was the word that sprang first to mind to describe the panna cotta!
Excellent fusion of Japanese with French / Western influences. Fully satisfied on the three times I've been here so far.

We had lunch here today for the first time and the food is delish. We were so hungry that I forgot to take photos. They have lunch specials for $8.90 and absolutely amazing. Will definitely visit again!
Highly recommend. Many different Chefs over the years I'm guessing, but quality and value has never changed. Always friendly smiling faces.
Authentic and delicious! Been here a long time and still producing some of the best Indian food in Adelaide

What a shame ....
We have been eating Raj on taj over many years . It was always great value for money and good taste . Not amazing food but as said great value for money . 
The last few time we ordered home delivery the quality has declined and the waiting time is a joke . 
We were told 50 minutes and after 6 phone calls to them it arrived nearly 2 hours to be delivered.  Cold . Awful nann bread as it was soggy . And all curries were cold and poor in flavor . The owner hung up the phone on us twice . The driver was very professional and calm . 
I think success has driven them to taking on more than they can chew . It should have been us chewing but after a few mouthfuls we threw the lot in the bin . 
Raj in taj you have lost a great client . 
Clients be aware there are many other great Indian restaurants out there and I would look at them first ... 
if you want cold , flavorless , and average Indian food then go to Raj on Taj 
Andrew
Beautiful Indian food served here. Very friendly and courteous service. When I was there, the food was so delicious that I ended up overeating, and could not walk straight for a solid half an hour.

Not a stretch to call it one of Adelaide's best...world-class dining and service, with careful attention to detail. Very talented chefs who can cater to all sorts of dietary needs - I thought being pregnant, it would pose a challenge but I did not miss out at all. The non-alcoholic drink pairing was very enjoyable as well. Highly recommend.

If I could give this place 6 stars I would. The place has a descent price tag but it comes with fantastic service, fantastic wine list and fantastic food. Food came in small proportions but there was enough of it and it.... was.... quality! Fantastic view of the vineyards looking over Adelaide. Great to celebrate any occasion. Loved it.
Great food and amazing wine selections as usual. Highly recommend a Bin 707 if you get the chance!

Booked for 7 people at 10am on Sunday, arrived at 9.50 and seated, pleasant lady took our drinks order, and said the waiter would come and take our food order, the fruit juice arrived after 15 mins, the coffee's took 47mins. The food order took 57mins to come for a normal breakfast, bacon was only just warm, the eggs were hot thank goodness.
My son takes clients there sometimes and warned me the service for coffee and food is very slow, good food when you get it, good waiting staff but very slow kitchen, it was 70% full, so there we no excuse for the long wait.

Magill restaurant is no good. It didnt help us get food after getting drunk from the tasting. They were apparently booked out. No one was there. All we wanted was something to soak up the wine so we could drive. Oh well.

Very nice dinner. We had the $95 degustation and enjoyed it very much. The quantity was satisfactory for the price and quality and there was enough of an experience to have me consider returning once again. Only thing was that none of the meals were really that memorable. The staff were very friendly and helpful.
My husband & I dined here mid week and had a great experience. The food was lovely, sommelier very helpful, staff attentive without going overboard. We'd definitely go back for a special occasion.

Tuesday 13/5/2014
Not the best experience at Auge Restaurant
Having been there approx 6 years ago with a group of five and had a reasonable meal but less than impressive service and a mix up with the account I decided to give it another go ( My mistake)
I booked for a group of 10 to celebrate my fathers 81st birthday This was a family dinner for a special occasion 
I was told that a table in the bar area would be set up as there was no room in the restaurant after some discussion re the comfort levels including warmth and noise levels and the amount of foot traffic  I decided to make the booking
On arrival we were presented with the table in the bar area set up with bar stools not chairs as any one there for a meal would expect I expressed my dissatisfaction with this arrangement and  the waiter responded in a terse unpleasant manner and told me I could have one chair only This was given to my father ( who is in a frail state of health and had an oxygen tank with him My mother who is 78 had then to sit on a bench seat also without a back 
This seemed a most unsatisfactory arrangement to me and was certainly not discussed at the time of booking 
We were treated as though we were there for cocktails and nibbles not for a dinner We were certainly not charged bar prices!
The service throughout the evening continued to be in our opinion substandard and most requests were met with slow and somewhat uncooperative  responses 
The menu was difficult to understand in terms of ordering entre choices and when clarification was sought regarding price per person it was not helpful at all The waiter attending our table did not communicate well in English I am still not sure how the pricing was worked out!
The environment we were seated in was a staff walk way and work area and was very noisy with bar work coffee machines and loud music which we asked to be turned down ( it was)
Our total bill was $1440.00 for a group of 10 We are a family that enjoys fine dining and have at least  three to four  group nights out per year and will spend roughly this amount of money However when we have been to the Lenzerheid or The red Ochre we have felt this has been worth our money This night was not at all
Not only was the setting  and service   less than satisfactory The wine list was limited  and for the price the menu is less than remarkable We came away feeling "ripped off" Issues such as paying $60 for bottled water when I specifically said ordinary water and one of my sons said tap water We were also charged for an extra main course I have not at this stage asked about that with the manager but judging by the night I do not expect a pleasant response  All in all a less than satisfactory evening and we will not return and would not recommend this restaurant

Stella & I took our son and his wife for a special meal having heard this was a good restaurant. We usually go to Alphutte and decided to try a different spot. The food was very tasty, but it stopped there. Portion size was just big enough to feed a sparrow. Table service was ordinary, wine service even worse - had to ask for wine glasses to be topped up, at one stage mixed our wine order up! And they don't stock crown larger. Left hungry and went to get a burger from the North Adelaide Burger Bar. Definitely not value for money. Won't be back!
Great service, great food.  Clueless bar staff!

Had a lovey dinner in Shiki excellent restaurant great food wonderful service from all their thank you very much. We always like this restaurant. Everything is lovely. Classic and well cooked. The wagyu the highlight and love that the French champagne is always a generous serve thank you very much. Mock tails for the children and everyone is happy.

Great service, lovely atmosphere made a great evening. I suggest not following the preset menu, but making up your own. This will save you a bit in the long run. 

The staff are very helpful to all your needs and will choose a great wine to compliment your meal. If you like butter and the aroma of gorgeously delicate foods this is a must have experience!! 

It's located inside the intercontinental hotel, 1st floor. And I suggest you come with a camera.
first time in shiki and won't be my last, thank you to Dennis and lok and the rest of the team for amazing experience at shiki kitchen.
Absolutely amazing, the food is delicious and the staff are very kind and go above and beyond to ensure a great experience.
The decor is looking slightly old and tired   The staff service and quality of food are still stunning and gorgeous
